after running the prometheus by helm you will run the pods and deployments
the configuratin of the helm will be present at configmaps

k get cm -n monitoring
kubectl -n monitoring get cm prometheus-server -o yaml | less
  
so to change or add the configuration rather than changing directly. we use the file and make changes init 
because
if we change directly. if deployment fails or cluster goes down we loose the date if we run the prometheus installation again

if we have the file we can run the below commands to make the changes to this config map i,e prometheus.yml or configuration file 

----
helm upgrade prometheus prometheus-community/prometheus -n monitoring -f current-values.yaml
kubectl -n monitoring rollout restart deployment prometheus-server

========

current-values.yaml
serverFiles:
  prometheus.yml:
    global:
      scrape_interval: 15s
      evaluation_interval: 15s
      scrape_timeout: 10s

    rule_files:
      - /etc/config/recording_rules.yml
      - /etc/config/alerting_rules.yml
      - /etc/config/rules
      - /etc/config/alerts

    scrape_configs:
      - job_name: prometheus
        static_configs:
          - targets: ['localhost:9090']

      - job_name: node-exporter
        static_configs:
          - targets: ['54.146.41.106:9100']

      - job_name: blackbox-exporter
        metrics_path: /probe
        params:
          module: [http_2xx]
        static_configs:
          - targets: ['http://54.146.41.106:30002']
        relabel_configs:
          - source_labels: [__address__]
            target_label: __param_target
          - target_label: __address__
            replacement: 54.146.41.106:9115
          - source_labels: [__param_target]
            target_label: instance

      - job_name: alertmanager
        static_configs:
          - targets: ['localhost:9093']
